  const renderAbout=()=><div style={{maxWidth:560,margin:"0 auto"}}>
    <div style={{fontSize:9,fontWeight:800,color:"#67e8f9",letterSpacing:2,marginBottom:8,borderBottom:"1px solid rgba(0,240,255,.12)",paddingBottom:4}}>ABOUT CDL WAR ROOM v25</div>
    <div style={{fontSize:12,color:"#94a3b8",lineHeight:1.8}}>
      <p><strong style={{color:"#e2e8f0"}}>VMP (Value over Median Player)</strong> is a proprietary impact rating for competitive Call of Duty. Named after the most iconic weapon in competitive CoD history (BO3).</p>
      <p style={{marginTop:10}}>The system uses a <strong style={{color:"#67e8f9"}}>mode-weighted composite</strong>: HP .58 / SND .31 / OVL .10, derived from regression analysis (R² = 0.936) against team win rates across 12 CDL teams.</p>
      <p style={{marginTop:10}}><strong style={{color:"#e2e8f0"}}>Key findings:</strong> HP is the dominant mode (r = 0.921 with series winning). SND matters but less than previously weighted (r = 0.595). OVL is team-dependent.</p>
<p style={{marginTop:10}}><strong style={{color:"#e2e8f0"}}>Four Dimensions:</strong> Skill (raw talent, 59% of VALUE), Impact (winning contribution, 41%), XFER (transferability), VALUE (fused overall). Grid-search optimal at r=0.9468.</p>
<p style={{marginTop:10}}><strong style={{color:"#e2e8f0"}}>Playstyle Archetypes:</strong> ANCHOR, OBJ PLAYMAKER, TWO-WAY STAR, SENTINEL, DAMAGE DEALER, ENTRY. Gun label does not determine playstyle. Flexes (55-69 hill) produce the most stars. Worst mode predicts winning better than best player (r=0.869). 2nd worst player is strongest single predictor (r=0.927).</p>
      <p style={{marginTop:10}}><strong style={{color:"#e2e8f0"}}>Team building insight:</strong> The optimal predictor of winning is 45% star power + 55% floor player (r = 0.948). Championship formula: 1 superstar (+4 VMP) + no liabilities (floor above -1.0).</p>
      <p style={{marginTop:10,fontSize:10,color:"#475569"}}>Data: BreakingPoint.gg + Call of Duty League · Model validated at r = 0.937 team VMP → series WR</p>
      <div style={{fontSize:9,fontWeight:800,color:"#67e8f9",letterSpacing:2,margin:"16px 0 6px",borderBottom:"1px solid rgba(0,240,255,.12)",paddingBottom:4}}>STAT GLOSSARY</div>
<div style={{fontSize:11,color:"#94a3b8",lineHeight:1.9}}>
<p style={{fontWeight:700,color:"#e2e8f0",marginBottom:2}}>Player Ratings (1-99 scale)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>Skill</strong> — How talented is this player in a vacuum? Based on KD, damage output, slayer rating, and SND gunfight ability. Ignores team context. A high Skill on a bad team means real talent being wasted.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>Impact</strong> — How much does this player actually help his team win? Based on VMP (mode-weighted performance). A player can have high Impact on a great team even with average talent — the system elevates them.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#fbbf24"}}>XFER</strong> — Would this value hold on a different team? Measures mode balance, LAN stability, and whether Skill matches Impact. High XFER = safe trade target. Low XFER = value is tied to current system.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#00f0ff"}}>VALUE</strong> — The bottom line. Fuses Skill (59%) and Impact (41%) into one number. This drives the OVR on the player card. A VALUE of 99 means elite talent AND elite production.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#67e8f9"}}>OVR</strong> — The card number (55-98). It IS VALUE, just scaled to a familiar range. Think of it like a 2K rating.</p>

<p style={{fontWeight:700,color:"#e2e8f0",marginTop:12,marginBottom:2}}>Performance Stats</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>VMP</strong> — Value over Median Player. The raw engine of the model. Measures how much better or worse a player is than average across all three game modes. +6.5 is elite. 0.0 is average. -3.0 is a liability.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>KD</strong> — Kill/Death ratio. Kills divided by deaths across all modes. Above 1.0 means you get more kills than deaths. The most basic stat but does not tell the full story.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>HP / SND / OVL</strong> — Mode-specific VMP for Hardpoint, Search and Destroy, and Overload. Shows where a player helps or hurts. A player with HP +5.0 but SND -2.0 is elite in one mode and a liability in another.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>cVMP</strong> — Cumulative VMP. Total VMP accumulated over the season. High cVMP means consistent production over many games, not just a hot streak.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>BPR</strong> — BreakingPoint Rating. An external stat from BreakingPoint.gg that measures per-map impact using kills, deaths, and team score context. We use it as one input, not the whole picture.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>GP</strong> — Games Played. More games = more reliable data. Be cautious with players under 15 GP.</p>

<p style={{fontWeight:700,color:"#e2e8f0",marginTop:12,marginBottom:2}}>Detailed Stats (Player Card)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>HP KD / SND KD / OVL KD</strong> — Kill/Death ratio in each specific mode. SND KD tends to be higher because there are fewer engagements and each kill matters more.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>HP DMG</strong> — Damage dealt per 10 minutes in Hardpoint. Measures total output, not just kills. A player can deal heavy damage without getting the final shot. Higher = more pressure on the map.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>Hill Time</strong> — Seconds spent on the Hardpoint objective per 10 minutes. High hill time (80+) means you are the anchor/soaker absorbing damage for your team. Low hill time (under 50) means you are the entry fragger creating first contact.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>SND KpR</strong> — Kills per Round in Search and Destroy. How many kills you average each round. Higher = more involved in every round. Mercules leads the CDL at 0.93.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>OD%</strong> — Opening Duel Win Percentage. How often you win the first gunfight of a Search round. This is the purest 1v1 skill stat — no team help, just you vs them.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>Goals/10</strong> — Overload goals scored per 10 minutes. Measures who is actually running the objective, not just getting kills around it.</p>

<p style={{fontWeight:700,color:"#e2e8f0",marginTop:12,marginBottom:2}}>Player Categories</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#00f0ff"}}>FRANCHISE</strong> — Elite talent AND elite production. Build your team around these players. (Mercules, Simp, Scrap, Abuzah, etc.)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>STAR</strong> — High skill, solid production. Genuine talent that would translate to other teams. (Spart, Kremp, HyDra, Pred, etc.)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#a78bfa"}}>SYSTEM STAR</strong> — Impact exceeds Skill. The team system makes them look better than their raw talent. Trade risk. (Dashy, Ghosty)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#34d399"}}>SOLID STARTER</strong> — Reliable. Not a star but not a liability. Consistent value. (Shotzzy, Estreal, Drazah, etc.)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#fbbf24"}}>SYSTEM FIT</strong> — Value is invisible to stats. IGL, chemistry, intangibles. Would crater on another team. (Insight)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#94a3b8"}}>ROLE PLAYER</strong> — Functional but replaceable. Average across the board. (Huke, 04, CleanX, etc.)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#818cf8"}}>UNTAPPED</strong> — High skill, low impact. Talent being wasted by team context. Trade target. (Sib)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#ef4444"}}>BENCH/LIABILITY</strong> — Below CDL starter level in both talent and production. (Envoy, MettalZ, Purj, etc.)</p>

<p style={{fontWeight:700,color:"#e2e8f0",marginTop:12,marginBottom:2}}>Playstyle Archetypes</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>ANCHOR</strong> — 70+ hill time. Absorbs damage on the objective so teammates can slay. The foundation of a team. Like a center in basketball. (Ghosty, Dashy, Abuzah)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>OBJ PLAYMAKER</strong> — 60-70 hill time. Does everything — plays objective, gets kills, wins SND. The most valuable archetype. Like LeBron. (Mercules, RenKoR, Kips)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>TWO-WAY STAR</strong> — 55-70 hill time. Produces in every mode. Scores AND defends. Like Curry or Brunson. (Simp, JoeDeceives, Kremp)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>SENTINEL</strong> — 70+ hill time. Holds positions and avoids getting exploited. Like a 3-and-D wing. (Spart, Cellium, aBeZy)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>DAMAGE DEALER</strong> — Under 55 hill time with elite damage output. Aggressive, high volume. Like a volume scorer. (Scrap)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>ENTRY</strong> — Under 50 hill time. Creates the first contact. Dies first so teammates can trade. The hardest role to stat well in. (HyDra, Huke, Pred)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>PICK SPECIALIST</strong> — Under 50 hill time with elite SND. Wins 1v1s and controls the pace. Like a lockdown guard. (Pred)</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>HYBRID</strong> — Middle of everything. Does a bit of each role depending on what the team needs. Most common archetype. (Shotzzy, Drazah, Nium, etc.)</p>

<p style={{fontWeight:700,color:"#e2e8f0",marginTop:12,marginBottom:2}}>Team Stats</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>ENGINE</strong> — A player who is positive in all 3 modes AND has VMP above +2.0. Engines cannot be schemed against in vetoes because they contribute everywhere.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>LAN Grade</strong> — How well a team translates from online to LAN. Based on combined BO6 + BO7 LAN KD retention. Grade A = team gets BETTER at LAN. Grade F = team collapses.</p>
<p><strong style={{color:"#22d3ee"}}>Mode Coverage</strong> — Whether a team has at least one positive player in each mode. Teams with a mode gap get exploited through map vetoes.</p>
</div>
